@flexiarg vsatelier/decision-provenance
@title Decision Provenance
@audience governance designers, stewards, programme evaluators
@tone analytic
@style design-pattern
@sigils [🔗/溯]
@references [vsatlas/three-layer-architecture vsatlas/stewardship-layer vsatelier/cluster-as-agenda]

! conclusion:
  Every decision that emerges from deliberation should trace back to the
  stories, links, and flagged patterns that motivated it, creating an
  auditable chain from lived experience to collective action.

  + context: You are designing accountability into a system where community stories inform real decisions. This does not apply to purely exploratory or artistic uses of the constellation.
  + IF:
    A facilitated session produces a decision — fund a programme, change
    a policy, allocate resources, create a new pilot.

  + HOWEVER:
    If the decision is recorded without its evidential context, it
    becomes an assertion rather than a conclusion. Participants who
    were not present cannot verify the reasoning. Future stewards
    cannot learn from the process.

  + THEN:
    Link each decision record to the agenda flag that prompted it, the
    stories and arcs that constituted the evidence, the session notes,
    and the participants involved. Store this chain as a first-class
    object alongside stories and links.

  + BECAUSE:
    Provenance is how deliberation becomes trustworthy. Communities
    that can trace "we decided X because stories A, B, C showed
    pattern P" are better equipped to revisit, revise, and defend
    their choices.

  + STATUS:
    status[sketch]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Define the decision record schema (decision text, linked flags, session ID, participants, date).]
    next[Sketch how decision records appear in the constellation — a new node type? an annotation on existing arcs?]
    next[Identify one real deliberation case to model retroactively as a provenance chain.]
